article.headline: South Dakota 42, S. Utah 20
article.story: EDs: South Dakota 42, S. Utah 20. CEDAR CITY, Utah -- Noah Shepard ran for 153 yards and four touchdowns, leading South Dakota to a 42-20 Great West victory over Southern Utah on Saturday. Chris Ganious rushed for 167 yards and two touchdowns for the Coyotes (6-4, 1-1 Great West), who gained 445 yards on the ground while holding the Thunderbirds to minus-4 yards rushing. Cody Stone completed 21-46 passes for 327 yards and two touchdowns for Southern Utah (4-6, 1-3). Nick Miller had 11 receptions for 154 yards and a touchdown, while Tysson Poots caught eight passes for 163 yards and a score. South Dakota mounted two sustained drives in the second half, culminating in Shepard s four-yard touchdown with 3:19 left in the third quarter and his clinching 13-yard score two minutes into the final period. Shepard and Ganious scored two rushing touchdowns each in the first half, giving South Dakota a 28-3 lead late in the second quarter. Shane Potter and Isaiah Dixon set up Shepard's touchdowns with consecutive first-down interceptions in Thunderbird territory. Southern Utah scored twice in the final 36 seconds of the first half, cutting the lead to 28-17. Stone threw a 21-yard touchdown pass to Miller. After D.J. Luchessi recovered a fumble on the ensuing kickoff, Stone threw a 16-yard scoring pass to Poots with four seconds left in the half.
